In an Asian society obsessed with wealth and success, one family in Taiwanâ€™s Jinshan dares to live on their own terms and has chosen a different path. A-wei, a 36-year-old ceramics factory worker and emerging ceramicist, and his wife A-xuan, a 37-year-old handmade soap entrepreneur, have crafted a cozy, minimalist home on a modest budget. These seekers of simple living have rejected the rat race and the endless chase for fortune, instead embracing a life of low desires and true contentment. In this episode, we meet A-wei, A-xuan, and their teenage daughter A-tong as they face the everyday challenges and unexpected rewards of living simply. What serendipitous encounter brought their paths together? Why did a once-cherished dream spiral into a regretful family saga? And how did A-wei's bitter childhood experiences nourish the soil for a sweet family home? Letâ€™s dive in and find out!

snippet.description: What started as a scary moment for this elderly lady turned into the most heartwarming surprise! When three young boys on bikes approached her and grabbed her bag, she feared the worst. But instead of stealing from her, they filled her bag with groceries, leaving her in tears of gratitude. Watch till the end to see how kindness can truly change someone's day!
